presence-marker — not the original transcript.

tools/parity-rate.ts classifies a phase invocation from the EXISTENCE of
transcript.log (the phase ran) and transcript-2.log (a single nudge retry fired),
never from their content. The live-run transcript is intentionally omitted from
this committed corpus; the classification-determining evidence is vendored verbatim:
prompt.txt (native vs fenced via the fenced-JSON footer) and the run's state.json
(runner + completed_phases). See test/fixtures/parity-runs/README.md.
